{"lemma":"كَعْبٌ","slug":"كَعْبٌ","root":"ك.ع.ب","root_slug":"ك-ع-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ع-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37031"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be full and round, to be swelling (of the breasts)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make cubic, to cube"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dice"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"knot, knob, node"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"joint, articulation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ankle, anklebone","examples":[{"text":"وَٱمْسَحُوا بِرُؤُوسِكُمْ وَأَرْجُلَكُمْ إِلَى ٱلْكَعْبَيْنِ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"heel","tags":["proscribed"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"high heels"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stub, counterfoil, coupon"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ferrule"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"die, cube"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fame, glory, honor, rank"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"breasts, bosom"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37031","headword_ar":"كَعْبٌ","root":"kEb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any joint, juncture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of division, of the bones."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  Also, [and more commonly, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ankle-bone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what projects above the tarsus, where the foot is set on;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what projects above the foot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bone that projects at the place of junction of the shank and the foot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, As, S, Msb;) each foot has two bones thus termed; one on the right and the other on the left; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of the two bones that project on either side of the foot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anklejoint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tarsal-joint;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joint that is between the shank and the foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, &c., Msb:) As rejected the saying of the [common] people, that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is in the upper part"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zahor","text_ar":"ظَهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) some persons say, that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of the two bones that are in the upper part"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zahor","text_ar":"ظَهْر"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so say the Shee'ah: and in like manner Yahyà Ibn-El-Hárith speaks of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiEaAb","text_ar":"كِعَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the middle of the foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoEubN","text_ar":"اَكْعُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuEuwbN","text_ar":"كُعُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiEaAbN","text_ar":"كِعَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAriyapN daromaA'u AlkuEuwbi","text_ar":"جَارِيَةٌ دَرْمَاءُ الكُعُوبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A girl the heads of whose bones are not big"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b4-  Also employed with reference to any quadruped; meaning, in a horse,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is between each"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waZiyf","text_ar":"وَظِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAq","text_ar":"سَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the bone of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wZyf","text_ar":"وظيف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the bone of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAq","text_ar":"ساق"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which projects backwards:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by this is meant, not the fetlock-joint, or hind fetlock-joint, but the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hock:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it has been shown, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euroquwb","text_ar":"عُرْقُوب"},{"kind":"text","text":", that the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaEob","text_ar":"كَعْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", with reference to quadrupeds, is sometimes applied to what anatomists term the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tarsus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaEobN","text_ar":"كَعْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaEobapN","text_ar":"كَعْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ossicle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one plays;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a play-bone; a cockal-bone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superior bone of the tarsus, called by anatomists astragalus"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as tali, a little bone, somewhat oblong, taken from the foot of a sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, thrown in play, like a die:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Lh, K:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"die"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faS~","text_ar":"فَصّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is used in the game of tables,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"backgammon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~arod","text_ar":"النَّرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any die that is used in play"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl. (of the former word, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiEaAbN","text_ar":"كِعَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (of the latter, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuEobN","text_ar":"كُعْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaEabaAtN","text_ar":"كَعَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K: the last so written accord. to the TA; but in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaEobaAtN","text_ar":"كَعْبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) The playing with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kEb","text_ar":"كعب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is forbidden (Kur v. 92]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  A conventional term of arithmeticians ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cube"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b7-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of clarified butter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lump,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compact piece"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutolap","text_ar":"كُتْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lump"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of dates [compacted together]: (M, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fidorapN","text_ar":"فِدْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece"},{"kind":"text","text":"of clarified butter, or of fat or grease. (TA.) ―         -b8-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is termed a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sum~ap","text_ar":"صُمَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is poured out at once,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what remains in a vessel, &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small quantity,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of milk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of clarified butter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A knot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a reed or cane;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is between each two internodal portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a reed or cane; (K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominent part that is at the extremity of each of the internodal portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a spear [of reed or cane]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an internodal portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion that is between each two knots,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joints,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a reed or cane: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuEuwbN","text_ar":"كُعُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiEaAbN","text_ar":"كِعَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b10-  By"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SArwA kEAbA","text_ar":"صاروا كعابا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the following verse,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"raA^ayotu Al$~aEoba mino kaEobK wakaAnuwA\n                      \n                     \n                        mina Al$~anoaA=ni qado SaAruwA kiEaAbaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"the poet means, they were divided and opposed in mind or opinion, so that each portion that was of one mind, or opinion, became a party by itself. (AAF.) [He seems to compare them to play-bones thrown on the ground; or to the several joints, or knots, of a reed, or cane; or to a spear not equal, or uniform, in the joints, or knots, of its cane-shaft.] ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumoHN bikaEobK waAHidK","text_ar":"رُمْحٌ بِكَعْبٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A spear with equal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniform, knots,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joints; not having one knot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joint, thicker than another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility, and glory."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN EaAliY AlkaEobi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ عَالِى الكَعْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man eminent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble, and successful in his enterprises."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaY All~`hu kaEobahu","text_ar":"اَعْلَى اللّٰهُ كَعْبَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God exalt his glory!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yazaAlu kaEobuka EaAlyFA","text_ar":"لَا يَزَالُ كَعْبُكَ عَاليًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May thy glory not cease to be exalted!"},{"kind":"text","text":"See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAlK","text_ar":"عَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elw","text_ar":"علو"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaA kaEobuka biY","text_ar":"عَلَا كَعْبُكَ بِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy nobility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glory, hath exalted me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  This signification is taken from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaEob","text_ar":"كَعْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a cane: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaEobN","text_ar":"كَعْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything elevated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Lh","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}